==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|atendre}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|attendere||to stretch toward, give heed to}} < {{term|ad||to}} + {{term|tendere||to stretch}}; see [[tend]] and compare [[attempt]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-attend.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛnd}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To be at an [[event]].
#: ''Failing to '''attend''' the meeting nearly cost her her job.''
# {{intransitive|construed with '''to'''}} To [[pay attention]] to; to [[commit]] oneself to; to give [[thought]] and [[care]] to.

